{"lemma": "بايِن", "slug": "بايِن", "root": "NTWS", "root_slug": "NTWS", "root_link": "/words/roots/NTWS", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun_prop", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n3675"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%86"}}, "translations": {"en": "separated", "fa": "جدا", "ur": "جدا", "tr": "ayrılmış", "id": "terpisah", "bn": "বিচ্ছিন্ন", "es": "separado", "fr": "séparé", "de": "getrennt", "ru": "отделенный", "zh": "分离的"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n3675", "headword_ar": "بَايِنٌ", "root": "byn", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In a state of separation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disunion;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "separated, severed, disunited,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cut off;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, * Msb;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboyanu", "text_ar": "اَبْيَنُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in a verse cited above, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bay~ina", "text_ar": "بَيِّنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN baAy^inN", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ بَايِنٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman separated from her husband by divorce;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Msb, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mubaAnapN", "text_ar": "مُبَانَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the former without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAliqN", "text_ar": "طَالِقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAy^iDN", "text_ar": "حَايِضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": you say [to a wife]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anoti baAy^inN", "text_ar": "اَنْتِ بَايِنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou art separated"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from me"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by divorce."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TalaAqN baAy^inN", "text_ar": "طَلَاقٌ بَايِنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a tropical phrase; and so is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaloqapN baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "طَلْقَةٌ بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mgh;) [signifying the same as]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taToliyqapN baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "تَطْلِيقَةٌ بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A divorce that is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as it were"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cut off; i. q."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mubaAnapN", "text_ar": "مُبَانَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the second and third of these phrases, and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mubaAnN", "text_ar": "مُبَانٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the first]: (ISk, Msb:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAy^np", "text_ar": "باينة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being here used in the sense of a pass. part. n.: (S, Sgh, Msb:) or it [is a possessive epithet, and thus] means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having separation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this kind of divorce is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one in the case of which the man cannot take back the woman unless by a new contract;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "nor without her consent."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MF in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bt", "text_ar": "بت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAy^inN", "text_ar": "بَايِنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bow that is widely separate from its string:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAniyapN", "text_ar": "بَانِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, M;) this signifying one that is so near to its string as almost to stick to it: (S:) each of these denotes what is a fault. (S, M.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biy^orN baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "بِيْرٌ بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayuwnN", "text_ar": "بَيُونٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naxolapN baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "نَخْلَةٌ بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A palm-tree of which the racemes have come forth from the spathes, and of which the fruit-stalks have grown long."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHn, M.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaAy^inu", "text_ar": "البَايِنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who comes to the milch beast"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the she-camel, when she is to be milked,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from her left side;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmuEal~iY", "text_ar": "المُعَلِّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", he who comes to her from her right side: (S:) or the former,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he who stands on the right of the she-camel when she is milked, and holds the milking-vessel, and raises it to the milker, who stands on her left, and is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmusotaEoliY", "text_ar": "المُسْتَعْلِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (T:) two persons are engaged in milking the she-camel; one of them holds the milking-vessel on the right side, and the other milks on the left side; and the milker is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmusotaEoliY", "text_ar": "المُسْتَعْلِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmuEal~iY", "text_ar": "المُعَلِّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the holder,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbAy^n", "text_ar": "الباين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buy~anN", "text_ar": "بُيَّنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T.) It is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaAy^ini A^aEorafu", "text_ar": "البَايِنِ اَعْرَفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolamu", "text_ar": "اَعْلَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who has superintended an affair, and exercised himself diligently in the management thereof, is better acquainted with it than he who has not done this."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 606.]) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TawiylN baAy^inN", "text_ar": "طَوِيلٌ بَايِنٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Excessively tall, far above the stature of tall men."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bay~inN", "text_ar": "بَيِّنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "S", "M", "K", "ISk", "Sgh", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}